              <div class="blog-item">
                  <a href="/en/notices/2018-06-06-navcoin-4-2-0-navpi-patch-notice/">
                    <div class="blog-image" style="background-image:url(/images/uploads/navpi-patch.jpg);">
                      <div class="item-overlay"></div>
                    </div>
                  </a>
                  <div class="blog-details">
                              <h3><a href="/en/notices/2018-06-06-navcoin-4-2-0-navpi-patch-notice/">NavCoin 4.2.0 NavPi Patch Notice</a></h3>
                              <ul class="blog-author-name">
                                  <li><i class="fa fa-user-o"></i>Craig MacGregor</li>
                                  <li>
                                    <i class="fa fa-calendar"></i>
                                      6 Jun 2018
                                  </li>
                              </ul>
                              <ul class="blog-author-name">
                                  
                              </ul>
                              <div class="blog-excerpt">
                                
                                  <p>NavCoin Core 4.2.0 was released today which includes the NTP server check to make sure every device has their system clock synced correctly when minting blocks. An unforeseen issue has been found when updating the NavPi using the updater script.
</p>
                                
                              </div>
